with respect to the economy. Kirchheimer picked 
up on this and, with his theory of juridification, 
described an analogous autonomization of the 
machinery of law while, at the same time, detailing 
its problematic expansion dynamics parallel to 
economization. 84 Max Weber demonstrated that 
modernity owes its character not only to the formal 
